1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Honeybees dance to share GPS-like directions to flowers.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:05,200
This is the waggle dance.

3
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:07,200
But how does it work?

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:13,600
The angle of their dance points directly to the flower, while the duration reveals the distance.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:20,400
Ethologist Karl von Frisch first decoded this in the 1920s, proving bees have a complex communication system.

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:26,400
Recent studies confirm that even slight changes in the waggle dance can affect foraging success.

7
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,400
Curious about more bee secrets?

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,000
Hit that follow button!
